{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The Anthropic-HH dataset (Bai et al., 2022a) comprises dialogues between a human and an assistant, focusing on helpfulness and harmlessness.",
    "The helpfulness data is divided into three subsets: Helpful-base includes 43K training examples distilled from a 52B language model, Helpfulrejection consists of 52K examples obtained via best-of-16 rejection sampling, and Helpful-online contains 22K examples collected through an iterative 'online' process.",
    "Each dialogue pair is labeled as 'chosen' or 'rejected' based on human preferences rated by annotators.",
    "We used 117K dialogue pairs for training after cleaning about 1K examples which contains no chosen response or includes \"Human\" or \"Assistant\" in middle of the context.",
    "And used 300 test examples out of 6K test dialogue pairs."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The Anthropic-HH dataset (Bai et al., 2022a) comprises dialogues between a human and an assistant, focusing on helpfulness and harmlessness."
  ]
}